Powered by RubiQube Ad Network A Senior Secondary one female student of Sedar College Baruwa has committed suicide after drinking Sniper a poisonous substance the police has said. A statement issued yesterday in Lagos Bala Elkana, Deputy Superintendent of Police, DSP, and the Police Public Relations Officer Lagos State said “On 30th May, 2019 at about 17:50hrs Ipaja Police Station received a complaint from Sedar College Baruwa that on the same date at about 9:00am one Favour Ekemedili ‘f’ an SS1 student complained of severe stomach ache and was rushed to the school sickbay. “The School bay immediately moved her to General hospital who in turn referred her to Lagos State University Teaching Hospital where she was admitted for medical attention. “Her parents were contacted by the School Authority and she died at about 6.00pm while receiving treatment.  “Her friends who witnessed the incident stated that, the stomach ache started when the girl took Fanjuice. That on a close check on the bottle of the juice, it was discovered that the bottle contained snipper chemicals but not juice. The chemical substances is being taken for laboratory testing. “Homicide detectives from the State Criminal Investigation Department are investigating the case.” Elkana explained.